assets.prompt:
Generate an RPG-JS scene event file for "The Training Ground" (ID: act1-scene4-the-training-ground).

Scene: Act 1, Scene 4
Location: undefined
Level Range: 1-2
Summary: The Training Ground is an open dirt area with chalk markings and practice dummies. Hana runs the player through two training fights, then teaches remix and broadcast at the Workshop afterward.

Trigger: area-enter, map: everwick, pos: 8,10

NPCs: Hana (npc_hana, dialogue: undefined)

Effects:
- system-message: {"text":"> - **Attack**: Strike with your weapon. Damage depends on your ATK stat."}
- system-message: {"text":"Some enemies carry trace memories. Defeating them can release these as fragments. (Boss enemies always drop fragments.)"}
- system-message: {"text":"Select 2 fragments of the same emotion to Remix. (The two Joy/Earth/1★ fragments are highlighted as a suggested combination.)"}
- system-message: {"text":"Remix complete! Two fragments combined into a stronger one. Remixing consumes the input fragments — choose carefully."}
- system-message: {"text":"Unlock: Remix Table Access (K-03). You can now use any Remix Table in the game."}
- system-message: {"text":"You broadcast \"Hana's Warmth\" into the workshop. Vibrancy in Everwick increased by +12! (potency 3 × 3 = 9, +3 emotion match [Joy resonates with Everwick])"}
- item-give: {"description":"Use a consumable from your inventory."}
- vibrancy-change: {"description":"Everwick 60→72 (crosses into Vivid at 67 — the player's first tier transition, triggering a brief visual bloom across the village. Flowers cascade, fountain sparkles, lanterns brighten.)"}
- quest-update: {"action":"completed","description":"\"Learn to fight\""}
- quest-update: {"action":"activated","description":"\"Explore the Settled Lands\" (markers on Heartfield, Ambergrove, Millbrook exits)"}

Quest Changes: None

Create the event handler that:
1. Checks trigger conditions
2. Spawns NPCs at appropriate positions using createDynamicEvent()
3. Plays dialogue sequences via player.showText()
4. Fires effects (combat, GUI, screen effects, music)
5. Updates quest state
Export the setup function as default.
